Preheat your oven to 150°C. Put the @lamb loin{2} in a #large bowl{} with a good drizzle of
@olive oil{1%drizzle}, @rosemary{1/2%sprig}(keep the sprigs whole) and the @garlic clove{1}(keep the skin on).
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Use your hands to coat the lamb then set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the potatoes. Halve the
@baby plum tomatoes{125}. Chop the @salad potatoes{350%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Trim the
@courgette{1}. Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length of the
courgette. Stop when you get to the spongy centre (discard the centre). Finely chop the
@flat leaf parsley{1/2}(stalks and all). Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks, discard stalks).

Pop the tomatoes on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @olive oil{1%drizzle}. Season with salt and pepper,
toss to coat then spread out and roast on the middle shelf of your oven until soft and sticky,
~{18-20%minutes}. When done, remove from the oven and set to one side. Meanwhile, add the potatoes to the
boiling water and cook until just tender, ~{12-15%minutes}, then drain well in a #colander{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, in a large bowl toss the courgettes, @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @olive oil{1%tbs} and
@sugar{1%tsp} with a pinch of salt and pepper. Blitz the mint, capers, mustard, olive oil and water with a
#stick blender{} until smooth. Season to taste with salt, pepper and a pinch of sugar. Set aside.

> TIP: If you don't have a blender, chop the ingredients as finely as you can and combine in a bowl.

Put a #large frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Turn the oven up to 200°C (once the tomatoes are out).
When the pan is hot, brown the lamb all over, ~{2-3%minutes} (leave the rosemary and garlic in the bowl).
Transfer to a baking tray and top with the rosemary and garlic. Roast on the top shelf of your oven,
~{9-10%minutes}. When done, leave to rest on a #board{} and return the tomatoes to the oven to reheat.
Return the frying pan to medium heat with a glug of oil (and some @?butter{} if you have any).

Add the potatoes to the pan and crush them lightly with a #fork{}. Fry, turning occasionally, until golden,
~{8-10%minutes}. Pop the roasted garlic from their skins, mash with a fork and stir into the potatoes,
along with half the parsley, for the final ~{2%minutes}. Arrange the potatoes and tomatoes on your plate
with dots of salsa verde in between. Halve each piece of lamb and sit on a bed of courgette ribbons.
Finish with the remaining parsley. Enjoy!